  <description>
    <p>
      SubSpace is a 2D space trading and combat game derived from Naev, featuring unique dimensional travel mechanics.
    </p>
    <p>
      You pilot a space ship from a top-down perspective, and are free to explore, trade, and engage in combat. 
      SubSpace introduces dimensional corridors that enable faster-than-light travel with unique risks and rewards.
      Navigate through SubSpace anomalies, build territory control, engage in multiplayer cooperation, and shape 
      a living universe.
    </p>
    <p>
      SubSpace features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Open galaxy exploration with hundreds of star systems</li>
      <li>Dynamic combat with various weapon systems and ship types</li>
      <li>Extensive trading and economic simulation</li>
      <li>Story missions and procedural content</li>
      <li>Ship customization with dozens of ships and hundreds of outfits</li>
      <li>Complex faction relationships and reputation system</li>
      <li>SubSpace dimensional travel with unique hazards</li>
      <li>Multiplayer features and cooperative gameplay (planned)</li>
      <li>Territory control and player factions (planned)</li>
      <li>Enhanced crafting and manufacturing (planned)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      SubSpace is derived from the Naev project (https://naev.org) and is licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later.
      All original Naev credits are preserved, and this derivative work maintains full open source compliance.
    </p>
  </description>
